{
  "uuid": "5351ced522f00c2a2518e3040df2ef5e",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "senior sales executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>We at BizChamp strive hard to provide our students with a proficient learning platform where they come and learn to live successfully in every walk of life.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>BizChamp International College seeks a driven Senior Sales Executive to lead student recruitment efforts and drive enrolment growth for its academic and professional programmes.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead student recruitment initiatives to increase enrolment in academic and professional programmes</li><li>Manage enquiries from prospective students via phone, walk-in, email, and online channels to provide timely and accurate information</li><li>Conduct course counselling by assessing students’ goals and recommending appropriate study pathways</li><li>Consistently follow up with leads to convert enquiries into confirmed enrolments</li><li>Develop and maintain strong relationships with students, parents, agents, and corporate partners to support recruitment objectives</li><li>Represent the college at education fairs, roadshows, and promotional events to enhance brand visibility and attract prospects</li><li>Achieve individual and team sales targets through strategic planning and execution</li><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of leads, follow-ups, and enrolment data within the CRM system to ensure data integrity</li><li>Collaborate closely with academic and operations teams to facilitate a seamless onboarding experience for new students</li><li>Mentor junior sales consultants by sharing best practices and providing guidance to enhance team performance</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2–3 years of sales experience, preferably in education, training, or services industry</li><li>Proven track record of achieving or exceeding sales targets</li><li>Proficient in basic computer applications and CRM systems</li><li>Availability to work on weekends during peak periods or events (with off-in-lieu provided)</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in private education or student recruitment</li><li>Familiarity with SkillsFuture, WSQ, or private diploma/degree programmes</li><li>Good understanding of the Singapore education landscape</li></ul>",
